<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=3900&amp;p=75523#p75523"><![CDATA[
<div class="quotetitle">mic_ wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />Unless you're able to achieve all the desired frequencies of your chord with the MUL and DT parameters.<br /></div><br />This is the case. Choices for MUL pairs are 2 and 3 (fifth), 3 and 4 (fourth), 4 and 5 (major third), and 5 and 6 (minor third), and a quick perusal through <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Just_intonation" class="postlink">Wikipedia's article on just intonation</a> will help you figure out why these work. These are also the valid choices for pairs when doing <a href="http://pics.pineight.com/nes/cheapsmb2underground.ogg" class="postlink">intervals on Game Boy channel 3</a>.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Wed Mar 16, 2011 11:16 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
